description:
Update opencode MCP client to auto-refresh JWT tokens.

Current issue: opencode.json stores JWT directly, expires after 1 hour.

Solution:
1. opencode.json stores client_id + client_secret instead of JWT:
   {
     "mcp": {
       "mcproxy": {
         "client_id": "agent_xxx",
         "client_secret": "yyy"
       }
     }
   }

2. On startup: call POST /oauth/token to get JWT

3. On HTTP 401 response: automatically re-authenticate

4. Optional: background refresh when token < 10 min to expiry

This is client-side work, may require changes to opencode itself.

Note: This task is outside mcproxy repo - track for awareness.
